<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,450,151,177]" box="[151,450,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,450,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,450,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Nielson" box="[238,450,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paralidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,350,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Paralidia</emphasis>
Nielson
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,222,498]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Medium size, slender species, male 5.50–6.90 mm, female 7.25–8.00 mm. General color light to deep fuscous, sometimes with black markings and/or large translucent spots on forewings; head narrower than pronotum; crown very narrow, narrower than width of eyes, anterior margin produced beyond anterior margin of eyes; lateral margins carinate; pronotum and mesonotum small, length of each shorter than crown; clypeus long, narrow; male pygofer with paired caudal processes; subgenital plate always pilose; aedeagus tubular, with shaft between base and subapex always glabrous, apex with 1–3 spines.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,222,498]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,439,463]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus is distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[684,844,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Armatoralidia</emphasis>
by the small pronotum and mesotum, and by the glabrous shaft of the aedeagus between base and subapex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
